Artificial Neural Networks

Michael Wattendorf

June 15, 2016

1 Intro

Our class as a deep dream.

There has been plenty of news about neural networks recently. You have seen how Google’s deep mind lab beat a Go champion and visualized a neural net, but there are also more worldly relevant examples. One of the most popular problems neural nets have been leveraged to solve is the broad class of image recognition. As you have learned, one of the most important parts of building a good machine learning model is figuring out what features are important and then collecting that data. In some cases, it’s not obvious what features you should consider or how you should extract them. Take this image for example, and suppose we want to extract cars? We really have a bunch of pixels organized in a grid.
